node.text:
In other words...keep on truckin'. 💛  There is no textbook way to experience growth. It looks different and happens at different times for different people. That's what makes us unique. 👉 That said, if you're ready to get unstuck, here are a few tools depending on what you're feeling:⁠
⁠
🙃  In a creative funk? A few minutes of quiet, controlled breathing or a walking meditation can help bring your mind into the present and open the way for new thoughts and ideas. ⁠
⁠
🙃  Stuck on a negative self-belief? Turn around the experiences that made your belief stick. Ask yourself: Who told me this? Was it repeated a lot? Why do I trust the person who told me this? Does holding this belief serve my highest good? Is there a reason to believe the opposite?⁠
⁠
🙃  Stuck in the past? Instead of trying to bury a bad memory, focus on the feeling it carries. The stories of our past don't need to be erased to discharge the emotional debt. Feel it to free it. ⁠
⁠
Inspire the community: What are some of your go-to ways to get unstuck?

2. We must cultivate comfort with not knowing what's next⁠
3. This includes releasing control⁠
4. #3 is made easier when we trust that The Universe always has our best interest at heart (even when it doesn't feel like it)⁠
5. When we surrender to the outcome, we make room for something better⁠
⁠

node.text:
Not-so nice to meet you, irritated. 😉  Can anyone relate? Let us help...⁠
⁠
If hot n' fiery Pitta season has you feeling a little agitated, you're right on schedule. Ayurveda teaches us how to adjust our routine and the things we eat and drink to cool down and find balance.⁠
⁠
Join us in the Chopra App for Dr. Sheila's new "Summer Renewal" series under "Personalized Practices." You'll even get a free e-book with tips and recipes to help you stay cool for the rest of summer and beyond. 🙌 Link in bio.
